      "workout_summary": "8m @112W | 4\u00d730s @264W / 30s rec | 1m @112W | 2m @278W | 1m @112W | 30s @331W | 4m @112W | 12m @291W | 8m @112W",
      "description": "In this test, the purpose is to record the best 10-min power. The warm-up consists of low intensity followed by some threshold toggles, then two priming efforts, then a maximal 10-min effort in the free ride mode. Try to pace yourself evenly - if you notice after 3-4 minutes that the power you are attempting is too high or low, adjust accordingly to be able to finish strong.\n\n- 8m 30-55%\n- 30s 95-105%\n- 30s 45-55%\n- 30s 95-105%\n- 30s 45-55%\n- 30s 95-105%\n- 30s 45-55%\n- 30s 95-105%\n- 1m 30-55%\n- 1m 30-55%\n- 2m 100-110%\n- 1m 30-55%\n- 30s 120-130%\n- 4m 30-55%\n- 12m Freeride 108-112% - mean max power\n- 8m 30-55%"
    },
